citations:
    citation-affc-brienne-vi:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "Brienne VI"
            text_from_source: "The septry stood upon an upthrust island half a mile from the shore, where the wide mouth of the Trident widened further still to kiss the Bay of Crabs."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Brienne, Podrick Payne, and Ser Hyle Hunt arrive at the Quiet Isle. They cross the treacherous mudflats guided by Septon Meribald and his dog. They meet the Elder Brother (a former knight who fought at the Trident for Prince Rhaegar), who reveals: Sandor Clegane died of wounds and is buried on the Quiet Isle (the large gravedigger); it was Rorge who wore the Hound's helm and committed the atrocities at Saltpans, not Clegane; and it was Arya Stark (not Sansa) who was with the Hound. The Elder Brother urges Brienne to abandon her quest."
